28/11/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia's President Branko Crvenkovski officially named Vlado Buckovski as the country's new Prime Minister-designate Friday (26 November).
He replaces Hari Kostov, who resigned earlier this month.
Buckovski received the mandate to form a new government one day after being elected as leader of the ruling Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia (SDSM).
He now has 20 days to present his cabinet nominees and government programme to parliament.
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik, Vest, A1 TV - 27/11/04)
